    "body": "I guess this rules bundling out then as you cannot really assign individually then, not that I need bundling it was just to cut down on the verbosity of the index includes.\n\nThat being said lets say I wanted to do as you have `window.$ = require(\"jquery\")` and the jquery file lives within `./libs/jquery`, now I know I can prefix it with a route like this, but is there a way to just tell the `require` method where the default path to look for modules on the client is? as this is the crux of my question I think.\n"
